p: The patient’s case reporting status was the primary outcome variable of interest, and was characterized in one of two categories as follows: 1 = reported; 2 = not reported. Patient characteristics included in the analysis were: age group, gender, race/ethnicity, rural/urban status [ 21], and year of initial diagnosis. The variables were recoded from their native categories to new categories as follows: age group: (0–30 years, 31–44 years, 45–54 years, 55–64 years, and 65+ years); gender (female, male); race/ethnicity (Asian/PI NH, black NH, Hispanic, white NH); rural/urban status: (urban, rural); year of initial diagnosis (Prior to 1990, 1990–1999, 2000–2009, 2010–2015).
